            <div class='post' itemprop='articleBody'>
              <p>Hi!</p>
<p>Currently, in redash when you fetch single row (by specific id) you get it in a table format.<br>
If you have lots of columns, it will be much nicer to show it as table where left row is “Column Name” and the right<br>
is “Value”.</p>
<p>Example in PL/SQL: <a href="https://www.allroundautomations.com/images/pls110sqlcomments.png" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.allroundautomations.com/images/pls110sqlcomments.png</a></p>
<p>I can submit Pull Request if you like this idea.</p>
<p>Thanks,<br>
Yosi</p>
            </div>

