            <div class='post' itemprop='text'>
              <p>For what it’s worth, while the front end world moves fast, we don’t <img src="https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"> Until recently we were using Angular.js, which we started with 5 years ago. We do switch to React now, but have no plans to move from it in the foreseeable future.</p>
<p>What I’m trying to say is that you can contribute to Redash without  burning out <img src="https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=9" title=":wink:" class="emoji" alt=":wink:"></p>
            </div>

